rComments: Great prof. I would recommend you take his class and really listen to what he says. He's a very smart prof.
He was the best professor ever! He is very clear and loves to help you out. His practice tests are very very helpful, and he loves what he is teaching. I would love to have him as a professor again!
Very nice and charismatic. However, test difficulty was many times not reflective of the past tests were given to study from (this was frustrating). Otherwise, a fair and good prof
One of the best prof at UTM...although he says "EPUS" funny, he is clear on his expectations.  Compare him to other profs at UTM and you will consider him to be one of the better ones.
he doesnt give proper expectations

For all you CCIT-ers...do not let this class, nor this prof, hinder your Want for this porgram.  This class misleads, as well as 100H.  No other CCIT class is this boring, this scattered and this diverse.  Because of this teacher I almost dropped out a program that I am now graduating from.  He does not care nor show any sympathy for students.
I had this prof in first year of university and I am now in graduate school. I can honestly say that he was the best professor I have ever had.

I had this prof during first year and he was so far the best throughout professor I've ever had during my school year.  Although his assignments are quite demanding, he provided lots of help, encouragement and guidance.  I'm in 3rd year now and still am relying heavily on his WRIT writing tips and other documents to get A+ on essays.

I had this prof in first year of university and I am now in graduate school.  I can honestly say that he was one of the worst professors I have ever had.  If you have a PhD in French literature you should not be teaching a course in communications.  Period.

Excellent Professor

Michelucci is a great prof. At first I thought I'd die from listening to his accent, but I suppose I got used to it. He runs a good class, and is an extremely nice guy to talk to if you need help. Also a snappy dresser, and loves "di littel ewalks.. you know, from star wars - di cute littel ewalks?"

This professor's writing assignments are extremely unclear which is a major problem, especially when most of the class shares this sentiment. I don't find him approachable and he comes across as very snotty in class going so far as to, in not so many words, call a class stupid.

After deaing with some of upper year ccit lecturers - especially the sheridan ones - you realise this man really knows what he's doing. Unlike most of other profs in the program, he gives you all the resources you need to succeed in his course.
Those who look for help will certainly will find it. This prof comes highly recommended, and is by far one of the best.
Super helpful and caring professor.  Very intelligent and profound.

This prof is amazing! In his lit. class, he analyzes all the books with you, and then for the essays, all you have to do is talk about what he already said in class, etc and boom, you got a good mark. He makes class interesting.Want to have him again!

A very organized prof but sometimes tends to rely too much on his PowerPoint presentations. He sometimes shows his lighter side to liven up his audience but his uncanny sense of humour only adds to the mediocrity of his lectures.
He is helpful and knows his stuff about the class literature, but I don't find him approachable.

Funny professor (dressed up as Neo for Halloween)! His random hilarious comments and actions are great. Very well organized. TAs for this course need some balancing, however. Some are extremely tough while others are extremely easy.
